Sounds typical of outgoing packet loss, so I'm going to give you the standard connection test reply;

Head over to the [Connection Troubleshooting Log Reader](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/209765743-Connection-Troubleshooting-Log-Reader). There, you can submit the Network logs from your match(es) and the log reader will show if you were having ping spikes and packet loss.

It will then will direct you to solutions. Please work through the solutions it suggests, and if you need assistance or they do not work come back here and we'll try to help.

You can also narrow down the source of latency or packet loss by downloading the [WinMTR Network Diagnostic Tool](http://winmtr.net/download-winmtr/), then use that to run a traceroute to the following IP (allow this to run for 5-15 minutes);

> 104.160.131.1

Sometimes all you have to do is reset your modem/router, but if you're getting packet loss on your side of your ISP you might have to contact them.
